						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone leaning against the front wall of the temple of Rāmaliṅga.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1048-49.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 970 Sarvadhāri,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1048-49.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of income from betel-leaf garden made by <hi rend="bold">Gālayya,</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Duṇḍa Chaṭṭa</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Ommaṛaḍi</hi> (modern Hommaraḍi) who fought with and killed the <hi rend="italic">daṇḍe</hi> (guard) of the (guild of) <hi rend="bold">Five-hundred-and-four</hi> <hi rend="italic">(Eleya-Bojaṅgas)</hi> when the <hi rend="italic">daṇḍe</hi> reviled this body.</p>						

						</summary>
